ent neoliberalism, providing food for thought for academics, students and advocates wishing to galvanise support for social citizenship in the 21st century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCitizenshipxPublic opinion. 0aCitizenship. 0aNeoliberalism. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311119634340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847429667423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847429667/original  a978-3-11-119634-3  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles